From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: cppmega.mlx <noreply@example.com>
Date: Sun, 3 May 2026 14:55:00 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] tilelang: T.fp8_scaled_matmul frontend stub

Adds a `T.fp8_scaled_matmul(A_fp8, A_scale, B_fp8, B_scale, C_out)`
frontend macro mirroring the audiohacking/fp8-mps-metal scaled matmul
kernel surface (Apache 2.0).

This is a frontend-only patch (no TIR op registered, no scheduler
changes, no C++ rebuild). It dispatches at parse-time:

  - Metal target: raises NotImplementedError with a clear redirect
    message pointing users at cppmega_mlx.nn._tilelang.fp8_msl_kernels,
    which wraps the audiohacking MSL kernel via mx.fast.metal_kernel.

  - Other targets (CUDA / ROCm / CPU): emits a placeholder call_intrin
    handle (`tl.fp8_scaled_matmul_fallback`). A follow-up patch will
    wire this through the TileLang scheduler to the existing FP8
    cuTe / TCGEN05 paths (PRs #202 / #1600).

Why a stub now: the full Metal lowering needs (a) a scaled-gemm
scheduler that fuses per-load scale into the K-loop, and (b) the
GemmMetalScalar machinery from PR #2118 to be extended for FP8
operands. Both are sizable; budget for this PR did not allow them.
The stub gives users a stable API surface today.

---
 tilelang/language/__init__.py |   1 +
 tilelang/language/fp8_op.py   | 180 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
 2 files changed, 181 insertions(+)
 create mode 100644 tilelang/language/fp8_op.py

